This product is a Svelte 5 port of and is heavily inspired by the API of:

  Mafs (https://mafs.dev)
  Copyright (c) Steven Petryk
  Licensed under the MIT License — https://github.com/stevenpetryk/mafs/blob/main/LICENSE

The component naming, prop shapes, and architectural decisions (root context,
adaptive sampling, namespace exports for Plot/Coordinates/Transform) follow
Mafs closely so that Mafs documentation and examples remain a useful reference
for svelte-mafs users.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

This product depends on the following third-party software at runtime:

  KaTeX (https://katex.org)
  Copyright (c) 2013-2020 Khan Academy and other contributors
  Licensed under the MIT License — https://github.com/KaTeX/KaTeX/blob/main/LICENSE

  KaTeX is used to render LaTeX in <Text> labels. It is declared as a
  regular dependency, not a peerDependency, because the version range is
  narrow and the API surface we touch is internal-stable.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

Portions of the adaptive sampling algorithm in src/sampling.ts follow the
recursive midpoint subdivision technique used by Mafs, which itself draws on
the function-plot literature.

If you build something with svelte-mafs, please consider also crediting Mafs.
